Great! 180 out of 181 tests pass. Just 1 failure in InstructorsController. The issue is that in the Create_POST_InvalidModelState_ReturnsView test, the instructor doesn't have CourseAssignments initialized, and PopulateAssignedCourseData tries to call `.Select()` on it, which causes a NullReferenceException.

Looking at the PopulateAssignedCourseData code:
```csharp
private void PopulateAssignedCourseData(Instructor instructor)
{
    var allCourses = db.Courses;


```

The problem is that `instructor.CourseAssignments` is null when the code tries to select from it. I need to initialize CourseAssignments as an empty list in the test setup to prevent the null reference error.

